Hi [baseline_arm_1][ce_firstname] [baseline_arm_1][ce_lastname],
Thank you for completing the electronic informed consent form for the COVID-19 study. Attached you will find a copy of your signed informed consent form.
If you have any questions of concerns please email us (EDResearch@health.ufl.edu) or call us at 352-733-1482.
Thank you,
UF Department of Emergency Medicine Research Team
This message (including any attachments) may contain confidential, proprietary, privileged and/or private information. The information is intended to be for the use of the individual or entity designated above. If you are not the intended recipient of this message, please notify the sender immediately, and delete the message and any attachments. Any disclosure, reproduction, distribution or other use of this message or any attachments by an individual or entity other than the intended recipient is prohibited.

redcap:Alerts.alert_message:
Dear [baseline_arm_1][ce_firstname] [baseline_arm_1][ce_lastname],

The result of your research coronavirus test from the UF Health COVID screening is negative.

This means that the test did not detect coronavirus in your system.

These negative research test results do not mean that you are not infected or won't become infected with coronavirus in the future, if exposed. We urge you to continue practicing ways to reduce your exposure to the virus or to transmitting the virus to others:

• Wash your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds

• Avoid touching your eye, nose, and mouth

• Practice physical distancing from others to limit the spread of germs

• Clean and disinfect frequently touched objects and surfaces

If you develop mild symptoms of fever, cough, or shortness of breath, call your primary care provider or occupational health physician for guidance on examination and testing. Should you develop moderate or severe symptoms, please do not hesitate to seek medical care, call 911, or present to your local emergency department.

Thank you for all that you do for the community, and thank you for participating in the UF Health COVID-19 Research screening protocol.

Dear [baseline_arm_1][ce_firstname] [baseline_arm_1][ce_lastname],

Please keep this email for your records. If you need to schedule another appointment, please use this link:
